Day-1 : Prologue

Important Points -

  -> Red Book if Westmarch - The Hobbit for more info, composed by Bilbo
  -> Bilbo - The first hobbit to become gamous  

About Hobits - 
  -> Hobits are unobstrusive but ancient.
  -> Good with tools, don't like heavy machines. They are possessed from the first the the art of disappearing swiftly and silently.
  -> The hobbits range from 2 to 4 Feet (They are smaller than Dwarves)

*** Bandobras Took ***
(Bullroarer), son of Isumbras the Third, was four foot five and able to ride a horse.


Hobbits of the Shire - 
  -> They dress in bright colour, being notably fond of Yellow and Greem. They seldom wore shoes, they had tough leathery soles.
  -> Mostly brown Hair
  -> Freely gave away presents and eagerly accepted.
  -> They live North-West of the Old World, east of the Sea
  -> Their earliest tales seem to glimpse a
time when they dwelt in the upper vales of Anduin, between
the eaves of Greenwood the Great and the Misty Mountains

__________________________________________________________________________________-

### Three Breeds of Hobbits ####

1. Harfoots - Browner of Skin, smaller, shorter, beardless and bootless. Hands and feet were neat and nimble, they preferred highland and Hillsides.
2. Stoors - Broader, heavier in Build, hands and feet larger and they preferred flat lands and riversides.
3. Fallohides - Fairer of Skin and of hair, taller and slimmer than otheres, lovers of Trees and woodlands.


# The harfoots -  
- were associated with Dwarves in ancient times, and lived in Foothills of the mountains.
- Moved westwards early and roamed over Eriador as far as Weathertop.
- Most normal and representative variety of Hobits.
- Most inclined to settle in 1 place, and longest preserved their ancestral habit of living in Tunnels and holes.

# The Stools -
- Lingered long by the banks of the Great River Anduin and were less shy of Men.
- Came west after Harfoots and followed the course of the Loudwater Southwards.

# The Fallohides - 
- Least numerous, northerly branch.
- More friendly with Elves than the other Hobbits.
- Had more skill in Language and song than in handicrafts.
- Old they prefferred hunting to tilling.
- Crossed the mountains north of Riverdell and came down the River Hoarwell.
- Ofter found as leaders or Chieftains among clans of Harfoots or Stoors.
